The paper deals with the problem of unsourced random access in a wireless channel with a massive MIMO base station, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.MM), and learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the use of compressed sensing and covariance-based recovery algorithms, which are commonly used in signal processing and machine learning.
